- Use `dotnet ef` to manage Entity Framework Core migrations.
- Update EFCore to the latest version using `dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore --version <latest_version>`.
- Implement asynchronous methods in your repository by adding `async` and `await` keywords, e.g., `public async Task<List<MyEntity>> GetEntitiesAsync()`.
- Configure DbContext options in `Startup.cs` or `Program.cs`, e.g., `.UseSqlServer("YourConnectionString")`.
- Use `AddDbContextPool` for improved performance in web applications.
- Handle exceptions using try-catch blocks when calling asynchronous methods, e.g.,
  ```csharp
  try
  {
      var entities = await _context.MyEntities.ToListAsync();
  }
  catch (Exception ex)
  {
      // Log or handle exception
  }
  ```
- Avoid common pitfalls like running multiple async operations on the same DbContext instance.
- Monitor and optimize your database queries to ensure efficient use of resources.
